    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8094194>
    dc:description "FIGURES 6–9. Details of Sarcophaga (Sarcorohdendorfia) spp. 6. Sarcophaga (Sarcorohdendorfia) whitneyi (Curran), anatergite, lateral view with anterior to the left. 7. Same, genitalia, anterior view. 8. Sarcophaga (Sarcorohdendorfia) isorokui (Shinonaga & Kano), distal part of phallus, lateral view. 9. Same, lateral stylus, lateral view of median part. Scales: 6, 7, 8 = 0.1 mm, 9 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: ha = harpes; hy = hypandrial lobe; jx = juxta; ls = lateral stylus; pg = pregonite; ve = vesica. [6, 7: Specimen from Guadalcanal, in NHM-DK; 8, 9: specimen from Bougainville, in USNM.]" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8094194/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

